text: Choosing your university courses isn't easy but don't feel forced to stick with them forever. After a year or maybe even after a few months you might notice that it wasn't exactly what you were after - that's fine! Be honest with yourself and follow what you want. Changing courses is very common. There's no point in sticking to something you don't enjoy. So try not to give yourself a hard time over choosing the courses.

I'm a curios person so I'm interested in quite a few things. Maybe I'm done with the film industry in a few years and then I move onto something else - I think that'll keep things interesting :slightly_smiling_face:
